/** @page example-index Examples and tutorials
@brief Learn by example to get quickly up to speed.

The examples assume that you have at least basic knowledge about graphics (what
are homogeneous coordinates, what is mesh, vertex, texture...), how GPU APIs
work (what are buffers, what is depth test for...) and basics of GLSL
(attributes, uniforms, vertex/fragment shaders...). Deep knowledge of OpenGL /
Vulkan APIs themselves is not required, as Magnum wraps most of the
functionality in its own classes.

Full source code for all examples is available in the
[GitHub repository](https://github.com/mosra/magnum-examples), see
@ref building-examples for more information. The
[ports branch](https://github.com/mosra/magnum-examples/tree/ports)
contains additional patches for mobile and web platform support that aren't
present in `master` in order to keep the example code as simple as possible.

